Last updated: February 14, 2026

This application is a testing and evaluation service.
Users have the right to request deletion of any data associated with them.

1. Your Right to Erasure

You may request that we delete all personal data associated with your account at any time.

This includes:

Account identifiers (username, email, user ID, chat ID)

Stored preferences

Usage activity records

Test content you submitted

Session and profile data

After deletion, your account will no longer function unless recreated.

2. How to Request Deletion

Email Request

Send an email to:

hephzibahadejumo@gmail.com

Subject:

Data Deletion Request


Include at least one identifier:

Email used in the app

Username

User ID / Chat ID

3. Verification

To prevent unauthorized deletion:

Requests must originate from the same account (in-app), OR

The email must match the account email, OR

We may request confirmation inside the app

If we cannot verify ownership, the request will not be processed.

4. Processing Time

Deletion requests are processed within:

Up to 7 days

Most requests are completed within 24â€“48 hours.

5. What Happens After Deletion

Once completed:

Your account will be permanently removed

You will lose access to stored data

Restoration is not possible

You may create a new account later, but it will not restore old data.

6. Backup & Log Retention

Because this is a test system:

Some system logs may remain in temporary backups

Backups automatically expire within 30 days

We do not restore deleted accounts from backups

7. Exceptions

We may retain minimal data only if required to:

Detect fraud or abuse

Comply with legal obligations

Maintain security audit trails

This retained data is restricted and not used for any other purpose.

8. Contact

For deletion questions or issues:

hephzibahadejumo@gmail.com
